      "title": "[CBC Arts] Meet the Canadian woman who was Matt Damon's stunt double in The Odyssey",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://i.cbc.ca/ais/cf34aefd-8fa2-4268-ae8b-bae42f59c21c,1784754930938/full/max/0/default.jpg?im=Crop%2Crect%3D%280%2C0%2C1920%2C1080%29%3BResize%3D620\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://i.cbc.ca/ais/cf34aefd-8fa2-4268-ae8b-bae42f59c21c,1784754930938/full/max/0/default.jpg?im=Crop%2Crect%3D%280%2C0%2C1920%2C1080%29%3BResize%3D620\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img alt=\"a side by side picture of matt damon in armour and devyn dalton\" height=\"349\" src=\"https://i.cbc.ca/ais/cf34aefd-8fa2-4268-ae8b-bae42f59c21c,1784754930938/full/max/0/default.jpg?im=Crop%2Crect%3D%280%2C0%2C1920%2C1080%29%3BResize%3D%28620%29\" title=\"Matt Damon who plays Odysseus (left) in Christopher Nolan&apos;s The Odyssey says his stunt double was a woman, Devyn Dalton (right) — a Canadian stunt performer.\" width=\"620\" /><p>Matt Damon's biceps in The Odyssey have been getting plenty of attention lately — but not for the reason some might think.\nDuring a recent interview, Damon was quick to confess that, in at least one key scene in Christopher Nolan's action-fantasy epic, those impressive arms–belonged to someone else.</p>",
